			<div class="article-correspondence layout-item fill-pattern-light">
		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1188">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>After I finished reading Viv&eacute; Griffith&rsquo;s essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4242">The Three Ages of Woman</a>&rdquo; [December 2008], I closed my eyes and remembered when I&rsquo;d been young and filled with the excitement of new love.</p>

<p>My man and I were summer-camp counselors in steamy Kentucky. I can still see his bare back glistening with sweat as he sat on the edge of the lake. I &ldquo;rescued&rdquo; him in the water-safety-instructor class. We cooked bacon and eggs over an open fire in the morning and snuck off to be together at night.</p>

<p>Like Griffith, I am middle-aged, feeling neither young nor old but in between. The young man of my memory is now my gray-haired husband, who traveled with me last summer to Italy, the setting of Griffith&rsquo;s essay. We prowled the streets of Rome, the canals of Venice, and the alleyways of Florence. We stood under gilded domes and in front of masterpieces in museums. Griffith&rsquo;s writing took me back to both sweet places and times.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Helen Henry<br>Olympia, Washington</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
		<div class="article-correspondence-cta">
		<div class="cta cta-l1" data-url="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">
			<div class="cta-intro">
				<h5 class="cta-title alt-ff">Thinking about writing us a letter?</h5>
				<p class="cta-text">Give in to the temptation. We love getting mail. <br><span class="xsmall">(Of course, we reserve the right to edit.)</span></p>
